PE businessman Christopher Panayiotou is accused of hiring men to kill his wife Jayde Panayiotou in April 2015. CAPE TOWN - The murder trial against alleged wife killer Christopher Panayiotou and two others has been postponed until April 2017.They have been on trial in the Port Elizabeth High Court for 36 days.The businessman is accused of hiring men to kill Jayde Panayiotou in April 2015. When the matter resumes in April, the court is expected to continue with the trial within a trial, into whether a recorded conversation between the alleged middle man Luthando Siyoni and Panayiotou is admissible. The conversation was taped during a police sting operation after Siyoni was arrested. In it, Panayiotou allegedly implicates himself in his wife s murder. The defense argues it is inadmissible as evidence because they claim Siyoni s confession was beaten out of him by police.(Edited by Winnie Theletsane)